[{'action': 'opened', 'author': 'abuuzayr', 'comment_id': None, 'datetime': '2021-03-19T10:19:07Z', 'masked_author': 'username_0', 'text': "Tailwind just released a spanking new experimental library for just-in-time compilations a few days ago: https://blog.tailwindcss.com/just-in-time-the-next-generation-of-tailwind-css

For me who's using an underpowered laptop, developing on blitzjs.com was quite a pain as any change I made would trigger a CSS recompilation and my browser would struggle to apply the large css bundle as we enabled quite a few variants (perhaps we don't even use all the enabled variants, but since V2 was a fork off the tailwind website.. we didn't look into removing the unused variants)

While the library is experimental, I think it is sufficiently ready and will bring a lot of benefits by this simple small change. But of course, this is optional and we don't have to apply it if we don't want to :)", 'title': 'Optional chore: Add and use @tailwindcss/jit', 'type': 'issue'}
